[1] Ukraine
Date: 7 Jul 2012
Source: UBR [In Russian, trans. & edited - Mod.CP]
http://ubr.ua/leisure/health/v-ukraine-zaboleli-koru-115-tysiach-chelovek-s-nachala-goda-147309


In Ukraine 11 500 people have contracted measles this year
----------------------------------------------------------
According to the Ukrainian Ministry of Health, the Sanitary-Epidemiological Service has recorded 11 427 cases of measles in Ukraine between 1 Jan 2012 and 6 Jul 2012, plus another 37 suspected cases recorded on 5 Jul 2012. Most of these new cases of measles cases were reported in the western regions of Ukraine. 14 cases were recorded in the Ternopil region, 6 in the Carpathian region, and 4 in the Ivano-Frankivsk region. But no suspected cases of measles were recorded last night in the city of Kiev. According to the Sanitary-Epidemiological Service 11 406 cases of measles were recorded in Ukraine between 1 Jan 2012 and 5 Jul 2012. Between January and March 6403 cases were recorded.

The Sanitary-Epidemiological Service predicts the total number of cases of measles in 2012 will approach 18 000. One reason for the outbreak in Ukraine, according to the Sanitary-Epidemiological Service, has been importation of infection from other regions of Europe where measles has been widespread in recent times. In 2010 only 39 cases of measles were recorded in Ukraine.

--
communicated by ProMED-mail
