The Americas
------------
[3] USA (New Mexico)
Date: Tue 3 Jul 2012
Surce: ABQ Joutnal [eited]
http://www.abqjournal.com/main/2012/07/03/abqnewsseeker/health-department-investigates-measles-case.html


Health dept investigates measles case
-------------------------------------
The New Mexico Department of Health is investigating a [single] case of measles with contacts in both Rio Arriba and Taos counties, according to a department news release. The department's Scientific Laboratory Division confirmed the case in a 9 year old girl who was not immunized against the disease and is the first confirmed measles case in New Mexico since February 2011, the release said.

"We are working with the patient's family to identify people who may have been exposed so we can prevent more cases of the disease," Health Department secretary Dr Catherine Torres said in the release. "This case should serve as a reminder to all of us to keep our immunizations up to date, especially when it comes to children. Immunizations are the best tool we have to protect people from serious and potentially life-threatening diseases."

